It's understood four miners were underground when the shaft collapsed; four others sitting above ground were sucked in and buried under. HARARE - The bodies of eight illegal miners have been retrieved from a collapsed mine shaft. The accident was first reported earlier this week and an operation to retrieve the bodies took several days.The tragedy occurred at Big Mine, in the gold-rich Mazowe district north of Harare. Earlier reports suggested that four miners were underground when the shaft collapsed on Monday night; four others sitting above ground were sucked down and buried with them.The state-run ZBC is reporting that a ninth miner survived because he d gone to buy provisions. The eight bodies have been taken to a mortuary in the nearby town of concession. Police spokeswoman Charity Charmba told the ZBC that people missing relatives should visit the hospital mortuary to identify the deceased.